inn1.comm: outswing to start, on a good length outside off. Smith kept his bat close to his body, inside the line, and let the ball go
full and wide, and Smith drives away from his body, uppishly, and it flies away into the gap between backward point and cover
shorter now, outside off, and Smith slashes hard and the edge bounces down short of Mohit at third man
gentle outswinger outside off, and Bravo lets it go
another outswinger, back of a length, and Bravo is beaten poking at it away from his body
fuller now, again in that wide-ish channel outside off, and Bravo leaves again
back of a length on a tight off-stump line, blocked towards short cover
length ball outside off, sliced uppishly towards third man
back of a length, comes in off the seam from outside off, and Bravo stands up tall and punches that handsomely through square cover
back of a length again, punched straight to cover this time
comes in off the seam from off and middle. Bravo can't quite bring his bat down quick enough to flick, and gets some thigh pad on it down towards fine leg

whoa. This is a superb batting pitch. That was only slightly short from Mohit, and it sat up perfectly outside off for Bravo to play that punch once more, straighter this time, between cover and mid-off
straightens from a nice length outside off, and good carry through to Dhoni after Smith lets it go
leaves Smith from back of a length, and he opens his bat face to steer it down to third man
looks for the inswinger now, and he doesn't quite get his line right, swings down the leg side
lots of outswing outside off, too far from Bravo to tempt him to play at it
and again. This isn't a bad one-day line, swinging it away from the fifth stump. Bravo leaves again
shuffles across now and pushes at the ball as it starts to curl away from him. Is opened up a touch and the ball goes off the shoulder of his bat towards backward point
outswinger, outside off, leave. Where have we seen this sequence before?
wide outswinger, fairly full, and Smith throws his bat at it, looking to lash that through cover, and the ball beats him by a big margin
back of a length outside off, punched to mid-off
full on off stump, and Smith looks to drive through the off side, but the ball goes off the inside half of his bat towards midwicket
looks to pull this into the neighbouring district from wide outside off. The ball swings away, hits the toe end of his bat, and bobbles towards cover
outswinger on a nice length outside off, left alone
another wide-ish outswinger, another leave
inswing from back of a length, cramps him up as he looks to punch through cover, and he ends up having to poke it away towards mid-off
the outswinger now, Bhuvi's teasing him here. He had a hard look at it, saw which way it was going, and pulled his bat away just in time
another outswinger, fuller this time, and Smith is beaten trying to drive on the up
another outswinger, on an off and middle line. Smith goes back and across and defends back to the bowler
beauty! This is angled in, back of a length, forcing Smith to play, and then it leaves him and beats his outside edge
wide, full outswinger, inviting the drive, and Smith gets forward but doesn't middle it, rolls down to mid-off. End of a superb over from Bhuvneshwar

keeps low, and this was angled in by Shami. The ball sneaks under the bat as Smith looks to jam down on it, and it just misses off stump and sneaks under Dhoni's gloves as well. He was a little slow bending
goes hard at this one, a little bit of outswing outside off, and he doesn't quite middle it, but gets it into the gap between the bowler and mid-on
whadaball! That was angled in quite a lot, and then left Bravo off the pitch, beating his outside edge, and then it swung away even more as it approached the keeper
fuller, wider, and Bravo lets it go
too straight now, and Bravo clips it smartly off his hips and sends it racing away to the forward square leg boundary
big inswing now, quite full, a little too straight, and it bounces off Dhoni's left glove as he throws himself sideways to try and stop it
inswing again from an off-and-middle line, loads of it, and it pings Smith on the front pad as he looks to flick
back of a length inswinger, homing in on off stump, and he plays with a straight bat to defend that to mid-on
outswinger wide outside off, and once again Bravo leaves it alone
beaten again! The angle is foxing the batsmen here. It's slanting in from wide of the crease, and then it moves away sharply, quite late, and Bravo's hands follow but his feet do not
this one slants in from back of a length and Bravo works it off his hips towards deep backward square leg
another pinpoint inswinger, curving in towards off stump, and Smith defends off the back foot
length ball, straightens outside off, and Smith stays on the back foot and dabs it away to backward point
gone! That was the full, wide tempter, curling away late, and Bravo throws his bat at it hard, gets a thick edge, and Dhawan takes a simple waist-high catch at first slip
back of a length, worked off the hips towards square leg
swings this away from Bravo, back of a length, and the batsman lets it go
again, back of a length, a bit of swing to exaggerate the angle across the left-hander, and Bravo lets it go
fuller now, and Bravo defends to mid-off
length ball, angled across towards the fifth stump, and it's left well alone
back of a length outside off, Smith slices at the ball and sends it running away to the right of third man. Mishra makes a tumbling save
goes hard at this length ball that swings in just a touch towards off stump, and he hits it in the air but it drops into no-man's land to the right of Rahane at cover
back of a length, tucked off the hips to the right of Rahane at short midwicket
shortish, just a bit of width, and Smith slashes hard and the top edge flies over the slips, one bounce and over the boundary
full, wide enough outside off for Smith to get a good stride forward and thump it cleanly over mid-off
short, wide, and he slaps it away to the right of third man. Mishra is sent tumbling again. He makes a good stop - not the picture of athletic perfection but effective enough
slants away from Bravo, who pokes at it and is beaten. Bounces just short of Dhoni, who sticks out his left glove and parries it
length ball, angling towards off stump. Bravo stays on the back foot and defends into the off side
swings away from Bravo from just back of a length. He comes forward and just leans into a straight-bat push that runs away quickly to the left of point
looks for the ball swinging the other way, and doesn't get his line right, swings down the leg side and tests Dhoni's reach again
this is the outswinger to the left-hander, starts on off and keeps swinging a long way away, and Bravo has no option but to leave
lovely delivery, on a fourth-stump line, fuller than the previous ball and leaving him very late. Bravo pushes at it and makes no contact
shorter this time, wide outside off. Bravo thought of cutting but decided against it at the last moment
beautiful. This was the perfect length, on off stump, and Bravo had to play at it and the ball left him and beat his outside edge again
and turn straightaway, beats Smith's forward prod outside off
goes on the back foot this time, and defends the ball into the on side
a bit of air outside off, and Smith launches it effortlessly over the long-on boundary. Such a lovely smooth swing of the bat
tossed up on middle stump, checked drive down to long-off
Bravo doesn't know how much this is going to turn into him from outside off. It doesn't, and it beats his outside edge
straighter now, a bit flatter, and he blocks it to short midwicket
tossed up very full, too full to see if there's any turn for him, yorks Smith on middle stump and he jams his bat down to poke it back to the bowler
back of a length slider on middle stump, tucked away to deep backward square leg
short, wide, slapped away to the left of the sweeper on the off-side boundary
legbreak outside off, slow turn. Smith goes on the back foot and defends towards mid-off
tossed up outside off, and it goes through with the angle and Dhoni fumbles after it beats Smith's inside edge as he looked to slog that over the top

looks to slog-sweep and misses, the ball goes through with the angle and hits him on the back thigh. Bounced quite a bit, and may have hit him outside the line of off stump. It hit him in line with off, actually, and was that straightening enough to miss off? Looked pretty close to me
back of a length on off stump, defended back to the bowler
slanted across Bravo, just back of a length, left alone outside off
back of a length, a touch too straight. Bravo can't connect with that nudge off the hips but it rolls off his thigh pad towards square leg
came back in a long way from middle and off, and the ball goes off the inside edge towards midwicket
back of a length, nurdled off the hips towards midwicket
slanted across on a fairly full length, and leaves him just a bit, very late, and beats the outside edge as he looks to drive on the up through cover
length ball on leg stump, worked away to the right of midwicket
fullish ball on middle and off, defended back to the bowler
tossed up on off and middle, defended towards mid-off
short ball, and he's on the back foot in a flash to smack that between cover and mid-off. Super shot
looks to sweep this fine, misses, but gets a wide for his efforts
a touch short again, and he punches it to deep cover
tossed up outside off, defended to extra cover
back of a length outside off, and Kohli dives to his left at short cover to stop this firmly hit punch
punched again off the back foot, and this time it's Mohit who dives to his right at wide mid-off to stop that
back of a length, angling in towards off stump, defended back to the bowler
back of a length outside off, punched straight to point

full on off stump, and it's driven very firmly, between the bowler's legs. Mohit stops it, running towards long-on, and looks to combine with the man running back from mid-off but his underarm flick goes wide of Rahane and they get an extra run
that's a touch too straight, and he plays a nice-looking pick-up shot to go over midwicket and find the boundary wide of long-on
pushed through, too close to off stump to cut, and the ball sneaks under Bravo's bat and bounces off Dhoni's thigh towards fine leg
goes hard at this full ball outside off, slices it over the gap between point and cover, and both fielders run back but can't get close to catching it
too close to cut again, and this time the ball beats his top edge and goes into Dhoni's gloves
this time it's just wide enough for Bravo to skip back and place that cut wide of the diving man at backward point
fuller now, on middle and off, pushed back to the bowler
length ball on middle stump, pushed down to long-on
full on off stump, checked drive between the bowler and mid-off
back of a length, angling in towards off stump, punched down to mid-on. There's a wide mid-on and a straight-ish long-on as well
fullish ball on off stump, pushed to the left of mid-off
length ball outside off, and he throws his bat at it and slices it in the air, but it bounces a few feet short of Mishra at third man
back of a length outside off, carved away to deep cover point
slower ball outside off, and he looks to slog it away but it hits the bottom of his bat and runs down to that wide mid-on/straight midwicket
tossed up, it's juicy, right in the slot outside off, and Smith follows through nice and full to send that soaring over the sightscreen

and now he swings across the line. Why? That went through with the angle, and he would have been okay looking to hit straight again, but he went across the line and missed, and the ball crashed into the stumps
fullish ball on off stump, driven down to long-off
tossed up on off stump, driven down to long-off
full on middle stump, driven inside-out to cover
fullish ball, angled in, and it's driven, not timed very well, to mid-off, who's stationed quite close to the batsman
back of a length, and he can't connect with that glance, and it runs off his thigh pad towards fine leg
back of a length outside off, steered away to third man
back of a length outside off, and he punches it to cover, where Jadeja misfields
length ball outside off, keeps a bit low, beats the bat as he pokes at it and bounces down to Dhoni
fullish ball outside off, stopped on Samuels a bit, and he adjusted and checked his drive to the left of mid-off
full on middle stump, driven to mid-on
tossed up on off stump, pushed to mid-off
tossed up outside off, driven to cover
down the pitch, and he clips it to short midwicket
good ball! came in with the angle and cramped Samuels, who looked to punch through the off side initially but changed his mind and defended back to the bowler
a bit fuller and wider now, and he carves it away to deep cover
length ball outside off, and Bravo works it with the spin to short midwicket
length ball outside off, can't quite time this drive, hits it straight to mid-off
back of a length outside off, superb fielding from Jadeja, anticipated, moved to his left from cover point and dived to stop that punch from Samuels
slower ball on leg stump, clipped to short midwicket
length ball outside off, pushed to extra cover
nicely played! That was back of a length outside off, and he opened his bat face and dabbed it very fine, and Mishra at third man had no chance of stopping that, diving full-length to his left
slower ball outside off, and Samuels waits for it to steer it down to third man
tossed up on off stump, Samuels is forward with a dead bat
nips down the track this time, Jaddu targets his pads to keep him from freeing his arms and Samuels flicks through to deep midwicket
good length ball, met down the track with a push in front of the covers. Soft hands
flighted outside off to invite the drive, Bravo obliges. Beaten and Dhoni fumbles. Stayed a touch low, but could have bent down
good length ball on middle and leg, Bravo pushes down the ground
pushed through on middle, turned towards mid-on
driven through the covers as he tosses the ball right up on off stump
hammered! Saw the ball loop above his eyeline, had enough time to wind up those arms of his and strikes cleanly through the line.

oopsy, he's gotten overambitious again! Looks forlorn as he skews the ball straight into long-off's hands. That's the second time a wicket has followed a six with the batsman looking to repeat the previous shot. Bravo sized up another flighted delivery, but this was drifting away a touch to ruin his timing
sneaks in a googly first up, Ramdin hasn't quite picked it. Looks to tuck it away after reading off the pitch and wears it on the pads
leans into a drive through the extra cover region
opens the face on impact with a tossed up ball and drives through to the sweeper

a bit of turn, but it's been pitched short and Samuels has lazily stepped back and slices the ball behind point. Gorgeous timing, but the placement made this shot. Beat the man in the deep comfortably
flighted on middle, brings the batsman forward to block
some turn again, this time off a fuller length. Samuels defends cautiously
goes for a forceful drive, but this is the quicker ball that doesn't let him time it
this is round-armed in on off stump, Samuels is on the front foot and defends. Gets an inside edge. Got too far ac]ross to that slider
flighted outside off, driven casually to long-off
goes back to a straighter ball on middle and opens the face towards backward point
flighted on off stump, Samuels gets forward and opens the face to get the ball through point
leans forward and pushes a tossed up delivery down the ground to mid-off

lunges across with his front foot and sweeps quite nicely. Hit it in front of square but a good boot from Mohammad Shami, running to his left from long leg, seems to have stopped a boundary. Rayudu does well too as he picks up the ball, which was barely a few millimeters from the rope.
launched again, this time he's put in so much power that the fielders can only watch. This was a length ball and it was dragged to the midwicket boundary with a sweep
flighted outside off, Ramdin is forward with a defensive bat
pushed through on middle, Samuels waits on his back foot, adjusts to the turn and blocks
stays back again to a delivery angled in on leg stump and opens the face towards point
slid down the leg side, he tries to nudge into the midwicket. Wears it on the pads
pushed to the left of mid-off off the front foot
flighted on middle, Ramdin is forward with a defence
round-armed in on middle, Ramdin was already waiting on the front foot and has to hurry into a defence
width on offer and Samuels has sliced it through to the point boundary. Lunched back deep in his crease to turn the googly shorter than it was and has met it quite late
another googly, this one fuller. Samuels was primed on the back foot again but doesn't play. Misses off stump by just a whisker
pushed through on off stump, drives down the ground
dances down the track, doesn't quite reach the pitch but lifts the ball nonetheless to long-off
slower through the air and targeting the stumps, Ramdin protects it with a straight bat
uses that shot quite a lot and to good effect. This time the sweep goes past the short fine leg fielder, but it's not quite timed
delicately dabbed to third man. A little shorter and outside off, taken advantage of
back of a good length on off stump, Ramdin keeps to his crease and blocks
dabbed into the off side as he meets this shortish delivery with an angled face
floats this up full on off stump, Ramdin is forward and drives to mid-off
full and outside off, driven with an open face to the sweeper. Seems those two needless wickets have jolted West Indies back to being sensible
lovely drill down the ground, but it's a little too straight. Mohit bends down to get a hand to it and mid-off does the rest
comes down the track, but Mishi pulls the length back. Samuels adjusts and lets it loop off his front pad
uppishly driven towards point as Mishi tosses it up nicely
runs down the track, gets to the pitch of a flighted ball on the pads and drills it down the ground
shouldn't bowl there and this time Ramdin takes a cue from the Samuels playbook and cuts behind square. Crisply done
waits on a tossed up ball and opens the face on impact towards point and skip across to the other end
leans forward and drives down the ground to long-off
slashed away to the sweeper, this time there was no finesse in the shot. Just pure power. Fitting considering the ball was short and wide
cramps him up on middle and off, Ramdin tries to use soft hands and dab it into the off side for a single. But Samuels spots the cover fielder haring in and says no
slower ball on off stump, lovely change-up, Ramdin spots it well though and defends tightly. It was that back-of-the-hand one that gets a little more bounce

gets a little more bounce than Ramdin expects as he hits a back of a length. Tries to guide it to third man, but the ball leaps over his bat and through to the keeper. Not too far from off stump either
another slower ball, but this time Ramdin nips beside it and steers the ball off the open face of his bat to third man.
fullish on off stump, Samuels punches it on the up down the ground to long-off
gorgeous use of the feet to get the the pitch and a free swing of the arms sends the ball clattering into the advertising hoardings behind long-on. Flat and hard and perfect
goes again and he's broken the curse! Dances down to the pitch of the ball and launches the ball well over the long-off boundary. Gee, those are short down there
pushed through on off stump, Samuels stays back to block
picks the googly on middle and off, backs away from it and taps it into the covers
that's the orthodox legspinner and Ramdin waits for it to turn away and cuts it through to deep point
tossed up and drifting in on middle, Samuels pushes to mid-off on the edge of the circle after those sixes and jogs a single
loads of flight on this one, just outside off. Samuels gets into a drive through the ground. Gets a thick edge that beats Dhoni. Umpire signals byes, strangely
flighted on middle and off, driven down the ground for a single
a little shorter and it allows him to jump back and tucks it towards mid-on
closes the face to turn the ball between midwicket and mid-on
backs away and tries to force the ball through the off-side field. Can't beat cover though
shortish, but not enough room to cut. But Ramdin is able to get on top of the bounce and chop it down to third man
lets the shortish ball come on and guides it away down to third man with an angled face
sneaks in a legcutter, Ramdin tries to slice it behind point but isn't able to
point in business again as Ramdin shimmies away to the leg side to run a shortish ball square on the off side
another slower ball outside off, Ramdin slaps it away to the sweeper

they've been using that region to great effect, but once or twice the ball seems to misbehave here. This one, pitched just back of a length, skids on and gains a little more bounce for Samuels' liking and he is left groping outside off.
tossed up outside off, driven smartly to long-on
targets the base of off stump, Samuels squeezes it out to cover
magnificent. What a way to comeback into the team. Runs down the track and launches the offspinner straight back over his head for a six and his fifty
flighted on the stumps, Samuels is happy to keep it out
opens the face as he lets the fuller, quicker delivery come on and slices it to point
advances again, this time outside off stump to drag the ball away to cow corner. West Indies getting a move-on and that lower-middle order looks quite threatening
bounce and seam away this time. Ramdin is left pushing with an angled bat, his feet going away to the leg side as well. Lovely bowling
that's well run! Punches the good length ball wide of mid-on and sets off straight away.
change of pace, and he targets the top of off stump with it. Samuels steers it to third man
banged in short, but he doesn't quite have the pace to trouble the batsman. Ramdin stands and pulls to deep midwicket
third man gets a workout again as Samuels stays beside a shortish ball and lets it run off the face
good length ball on off stump, Ramdin keeps to the crease and blocks and the umpires call drinks onto the field
wanted a stroll to the other end with a slice to third man, but he's not able to get the ball behind point
full and outside off, Samuels keeps to the crease and hammers it to point. Didn't time it well enough.
this is the offcutter, but it's on a length and allows the batsman to go for a heave. Again he hasn't timed it well. But he's managed to place it well wide of the sweeper. Good work from Rayudu
that's a lovely drive from Ramdin, saw width outside off and drills it through the off-side ring. Sweeper gets into the act again
back of a length and outside off, Samuels was looking to pull but reins that impulse in as he realises it doesn't have enough room. Flat-bats down the ground
that's a slower ball gone wrong! Loopy full toss well outside off, Ramdin takes full toll to slap it over point. Rayudu was the man there and he leaps as high as he could, but it sails over his head
slogs from his hips as he meets a length ball with enough force to beat mid-on. Mohit runs after it, pulls out a dive but is still unable to pull it back
Back of a length on off stump, not allowing the batsman any room. Samuels inside edges a punch down the ground

that's been chopped away behind point. First bounce was on the pitch and it leaps away to the left of point. Third man is too fine to stop it. Who cares if he doesn't have room, he'll make some for himself. Stunning shot
this is slower and fuller, Samuels, almost as if he read the bowler's mind, knocks it into the point region with soft hands and sets off

not the best work there from Rayudu at deep square leg. This was a short ball but Ramdin didn't bother moving off his front foot. Unleashes a pull and it has enough behind it to beat a bit of a lazy slide
lovely reply from the bowler. Gets some lift off this deck to beat Ramdin's intended dab to third man
back of a length on off stump, gets back and opens the face for a single. Looks bewildered when Samuels does not respond
bowls nice and slow on middle, Samuels gets forward to block. Inside edge skews to square leg. Ramdin wanted a single and had hared down, Dhawan hurls in the throw but misses his target
gets down the track, but Jaddu has spotted it and pulled his length back and cramps him up for room. Can only defend
slower through the air on off stump, defended behind point for a single
moves away outside leg after seeing mid-off coming into the circle and lofts this good length ball from leg stump over extra cover
good length ball speared in on middle, Samuels blocks
that's lucky. Sized up a length ball, planted his front leg down the pitch and swung as hard as he could. All to no avail.

another slower length ball on middle, Ramdin waits just a touch longer and hammers the pull to the left of midwicket. Powerfully struck, but Rayudu pulls out a good dive and parries the ball away. Again, the ball stops millimeters from the skirting.
good ball, finds the wide yorker to perfection and it is a lovely counter to Samuels making room for himself. Beats him

threaded the gap between backward point and cover point. Usually when you see a full toss, you go after it with a ruthless fury. Samuels though waits on it, gets the angled face of the bat down and lets his timing take over.

pulls all the pace off the ball and Samuels this time is lured into making that mistake of wanting to hit the ball too hard. Swings blind and misses comically. He realises it too, flashes a big smile at the camera or more likely his non-striker
encore of slower balls from Mohit, this one is met with a push towards mid-off
pushed through on leg stump, Samuels tucks it through square leg
goes back and pushes wide of long-on. This was round-armed in. Back to bowling darts it would seem
that's terrible, Dhoni can't get down the leg side fast enough. Not that this was his fault. Ridiculous ball from Jadeja as one of his quicker ones goes well down leg

"how was that," yells Dhoni? Was this the plan off the previous ball? Stumping appeal goes up to the third umpire. This was pushed through as well and Samuels was looking for a flick. The keeper had nipped down leg quicker this time and whips off the bails, hoping for the batsman to overbalance. Samuels does not make that mistake. Should be not-out
slid down the pads, Samuels is able to turn it away through midwicket
round-armed in on leg stump as he saw the batsman making some room. Ramdin is cramped and has to settle for dabbing it down the pitch
fired down the leg side, a little too quick for Ramdin and his sweep. Too quick for Dhoni as well. And as it happens for Mohit Sharma at short fine leg.
flighted on off stump, leans into a drive through the covers

he was more than duped by this ball, was in the middle of a split too. But the slice behind third man is still as sweet. He had come down the track, but Mishi's bowled quicker and flatter. Samuels just about manages to adjust

oh, Bhuvi! He's dived over the dab to third man and seems to be in a bit of discomfort again. He's going off the field. Samuels gets another change to practice his late cut. Bhuvi set off quickly, then realises he has a little time and slows down, but does too much of that and has to hurry back up. Finally launches into a dive. All to nothing
sliced away to the man sweeping on the off side boundary
gets forward to the pitch of a loopy legspinner and drives to long-off
loads of width on offer and Samuels gets back and across and slaps it away to the left of the fielder
pushed through on middle and leg, tapped down the ground to long-on
full and wide outside off, Ramdin has slugged it into the covers. Amazing timing from Ramdin again, but Vijay at extra cover does a good job
back of a length and outside off, Samuels steers it through the point region
full on off stump, Samuels clears his front leg to slog the ball away through midwicket. That is where the ball goes but its off the inside edge
that's a top shot! He cleared his front leg and was waiting deep in his crease to get under a half-volley outside off. Clubbed it to the left of long-off with great power
banged in on middle, Samuels is a little surprised by it. Was on the front foot and he was a little late on the pull. Misses
seeks the blockhole on off stump, misses by a few inches and sets up the batsman for a slice through the covers
shorter and outside off, Samuels has cut it to the man in the deep at point
short again, Ramdin goes back and pulls wide of long-on. Not quite timed though
lovely, loopy legspinner outside off. Ramdin gets onto his sweep but the shot across the line and against the turn doesn't come off
good length ball on off stump, tapped away down to long-off
short and wide outside off, cut away strongly behind point. That shot has been a recurring theme through this innings and they've beaten the sweeper more often than not
googly, tossed up well outside off, Ramdin was to reach out and slaps it into the covers
good length ball, but it is slower on middle. Ramdin shuffles across and whips it away through midwicket for another half-century.
another slower ball just outside off, nudged away to short third man.
clears his front leg and slogs wildly, doesn't connect with the slog sweep. Back of the hand slower ball works again
back of a length and outside off, slapped away through point. Not enough room but he backed away and made his own and then fast hands did the rest
wants the big bludgeon, but the slower ball is too full and he gets an inside edge behind square leg
waits on a slower ball outside off and chops it in front of point to retain strike
pushed through and sliding well down leg. Jaddu thinks he's wrapped Samuels up in a lovely little bow. Appeals repeatedly and the ump doesn't budge.
tossed up on the pads, Samuels defends

that's it. A little nudge down the ground gets him to a century! Pulls his helmet off and sends out a roar! How is that for a statement, comes back and holds the side together with a well-composed innings. Incredible effort
runs at the spinner and launches it straight down the ground. No turn for Jadeja, no risk for Ramdin as he swings through the line and puts in all his power.
fired in on the pads, Ramdin loads up the the slog sweep and misses. Could have hit that down the ground too
pushed through on leg stump, Ramdin keeps it out

full on off stump, Samuels likes that length and smokes it wide of long-off. Cleared his front leg to get underneath the ball and lets his power do the rest. Before he was dabbing and nudging, now he's bludgeoning
lands the yorker on off stump well, Samuels can only jam his bat down to protect his stumps
backs away to a fuller ball on off stump and smokes it down to long-off. Right, time for the long handle

low full toss on off stump, Ramdin gets down on one-knee to slog it away. He wanted midwicket, but the bat face opens on impact and instead he finds long-on. Jadeja is a safe pair of hands in the outfield

another low full toss, but Samuels has stayed upright and beside the ball and square drives it away to the boundary. Amazing shot. He has been finding gaps square on the off side with increasing efficiency. Ramdin applauds from the dressing room
manages to nail a yorker on off stump, Samuels can only slice it through to point
nips down the track, but Mishra doesn't give it enough air. Pollard has to settle into a defensive push
no such courtesy this time as he sees the googly tossed up on off stump, goes for a slog but ends up inside edging it behind square leg
another googly, pushed through on leg stump. Samuels isn't able to flick it away. But he will take a single off the ricochet from the pads
fired in on off stump, Pollard gets down the track and slugs it down the ground. Bursts through the bowler's hands

just a little short in length and Samuels is back, opens himself up and slaps it behind point. Raina runs after it from the covers, dives headlong after the ball and slaps it back into the field of play
fullish on the stumps, pushed down the ground calmly
fires in a yorker outside off from around the wicket, Samuels tries to slice it through point again, there are four fielders there, but misses
length on leg stump, Samuels backs away slogs it to long-on

137 kph, middle and leg goes for a toss! Pollard, why would he go for a lap sweep? Well, possibly because there was no-one at fine leg. Either ways. he's more powerful down the ground. And this wasn't the ball to get cheeky. Only manages to give free passage to the ball as he gets down on one-knee outside off
full toss, a bit of a high one, on middle and leg. Russell launches it down the ground towards long-on
low full toss on off stump, Samuels backs away and slaps it to long-off
full on off stump, he gets under the ball, a little too much actually. Slices it up into the air and Virat Kohli at long-off steadies himself under and reverse-cups it cleanly
full and slid across the right-hander from around the wicket. Sammy pokes and misses
pulls the pace off this fuller ball on off stump, Sammy was into his loft too early. Gets a bit of a leading edge that lobs over extra cover
gets back, stays beside the length ball and slices it straight to cover point. The field is packed over there, there's a backward point and a short third man as well
back-of-the-hand slower ball goes awry as he sends down a full toss well wide of leg stump

he's struck it in front of point this time! Samuels has been unstoppable on the off side, doesn't matter if this was a slower ball, it had the width he wanted and he has slapped it away to the boundary
good length ball outside off, Samuels looks to flat bat it down the ground. Only manages an inside edge, which Dhoni fumbles behind the stumps. Seems to limp right after diving after it
that's very well bowled. This was the stock ball and it was hurtling at the base of middle stump. Sammy manages to get his bat down in time

lobs up a 134 kph full toss at the body, Sammy is cramped for room as he looks to slog it away. Gets an inside edge onto the thigh. Rubs it as he runs through for a single. Wasn't quite above the waist though
clap from Shastri at the dug out as Shami finds the block hole on leg stump. Terrific bowling. Keeps Samuels quiet
gets under it this time! Didn't miss the mark by much but Samuels was waiting with his balance back, summons stunning power to clear long-off by miles
looks for a swat through midwicket, but ends up with an inside edge behind square leg to equal his highest score in ODIs

in the slog for Sammy, he clears his front leg and launches it wide of long-off. Kohli runs to his left and leaps up. Not far enough though, he thought it was an easier catch than that. Ball bursts through his hands for a six
finds the yorker on leg stump, squeezes it out wide of long-on and gets a single to end the innings

inn2.comm: starts with an outswinger well outside off on length, Rahane watches it go to the keeper
touch closer to off and a bit shorter too, Rahane leaves again
fullish delivery towards the off stump, Rahane pushes it back gently
beaten outside off, loud appeal from Rampaul! Beautiful ball outside of with a bit of shape going away, Rahane looked to push but was beaten by the movement
back of length outside off again, Rahane connects but with a thick edge to third man for one
back of length on midlde and off and coming into the batsman, he pushes it towards mid-off and denies the single after taking a step down the pitch
starts with a short ball at 135kph on middle, Rahane ducks under it
he chases and misses again! It was on back of length outside off and shaping away, Rahane pushed at it without much footwork and the ball had good bounce to go over the bat
fuller this time outside off and swinging away, he leans forward and leaves this time
back of length outside off, Rahane gets an inside edge onto the pads while looking to push it on off, they scamper for a run as the ball goes to the leg side
swings it in form back of length on middle, Dhawan stays back and defends it back
on the pads this time on length, helped towards fine leg with the swing for two and he's off the mark
length ball shaping away from outside off, pushed wide of a diving fielder at point for one
135kph, right on middle stump on length, no room on offer and Dhawan defends it back
similar delivery, a touch fuller on middle and a solid defence from Dhawan again

chance for a run out! Dhawan got a bit of room outside off and pushed it to cover and wanted one, he was halfway down the pitch but Rahane was not interested. DJ picked the ball at cover and threw to the keeper but Dhawan dived to make it in time. Direct hit would have made it tighter
length ball on middle stump again, pushed down to mid-on now
good-length ball on middle with a bit of angle, pushed down to mid-off this time without much footwork
142kph, length ball with a bit of shape outside off, Rahane goes back and defends on the off side
short ball now and Rahane pulls it for four! It was outside off but Rahane stayed back and pulled using his wrists instead of hammering it, wide of square leg for four
outswing outside off again, he runs it down to third man with an open face for one
the ball is wide too outside off, slightly short as well, Dhawan chases and misses
back of length just outside leg stump, tucked off the back foot towards midwicket for a quick one
short again outside off, fuller than the one that was pulled, but it's short enough and Rahane pulls this over square leg for another four
typical Dhawan! Width on offer outside off and he caresses that between backward point and cover point for a four, nobody moved
slightly wide outside off again with some swing, Dhawan punches again but gets an inside edge this time close to the stumps
slower ball at 118kph well outside off, Dhawan crashes it through the covers but that fielder who just went deep collects easily
back of length around off and angled in, tucked towards midwicket for a quick single
another edge for Dhawan - shaping away from outside off and the edge drops close to Dhawan
outside off with some room, punched to short cover without any footwork
and look where he plays it! It's pitched up on the pads and Rahane delicately flicks it fine down the leg side to beat short fine leg for four. Poor delivery after that field change
what a reply, beaten completely! On length outside off, Rahane was squared up while defending on the back foot as the ball swung away to nearly kiss the off stump
brings it in a bit this time towards middle stump, pushed to mid-on where Benn dives to save a few runs
on the other side of short fine leg now, four more! It's on the pads again and Rahane cashes in to tuck it to the left of short fine leg who's in the circle
wide down the leg side and they run a bye too
full and wide, Dhawan goes for an extravagant drive but doesn't middle it as it goes to cover
goes across towards off for the widish delivery and pushes it to mid-off who throws the ball to the bowler's end to get Rahane back in the crease
brings it in from outside off, Rahane takes a step down and pushes it easily wide of cover for one. There's a sweeper cover in place
slower at 121kph, Dhawan saw room outside off and punched it fiercely after waiting for it, but straight to short cover where Sammy takes a blow
fuller outside off, Dhawan tries a drive down on one knee but can't connect this time. He's not looking comfortable today, not middling many deliveries
moves across towards off, Rampaul bowls it wide outside off but it's too wide and goes to first slip for an extra
fine leg is in and it's pitched slightly short outside leg, Dhawan stays back and pull-whips it while pivoting on the back foot and finds the gap wide of short fine leg for four
slightly slower at 124kph, he rolled his fingers over this one to pitch it on length outside off, Dhawan pushes it towards cover point
fuller outside off, Dhawan drives it in the gap to find deep point for one and keeps strike

back of length towards middle and that's very well placed by Dhawan! He went back, waited for it and whipped it between midwicket and square leg for four. Dwayne Smith was on the chase but gave up when it looked like he had a chance there
outside off this time, Dhawan gets another edge in an attempt to drive it
short and wide outside off, Dhawan chases without footwork and misses again. He's having a touch day
slower delivery at 113kph, full and outside off, Dhawan misses again while driving it
length ball outside off with the angle, he wants to crash it through the covers but fails to middle again
charges down the track to attack, but there's not much room and he punches but manages it to point
back of length and coming in form outside off, punched off the back foot to sweeper cover for one
doesn't use force like he was trying in the previous over, just guides it past backward point for four! He got room outside off, got the angle and opened the face of the bat to beat third man too
fuller delivery outside off, he moves across and drives to deep cover for one. Looked more confident on that occasion

oh there's a run out, both batsmen at the same end! Rahane tapped the length ball on the pads between short fine leg and square leg, they took the first run quickly and Rahane wanted the second so he continued to run hard while Dhawan went back after taking a step and both were at the keeper's end, Rahane has to go back. The throw was at the keeper's end but Ramdin quickly threw it to Rampaul at the other end
room offered again, he waits for it on the back foot and cuts it late to beat backward point and then third man by bisecting the gap for four more
slightly slower at 125kph, offcutter outside off, pushed off the back foot to point
full delivery outside off with outswing, Kohli lets it go
139kph, angled in from outside off on length, Kohli goes back and defends it back
angled towards the pads, he waits and flicks it wide of mid-on to get off the mark
137kph, length ball outside off, he leans forward and presents a solid defence to cover

this one straightens and Kohli's gone! He bowled it with the angle from outside off, it held its line a bit as Kohli went on the back foot to defend with an angled bat and the outside edge flew to Sammy at wide slip for a low catch near his right foot
shaping away from length outside off, Rayudu lets it go
120kph, length ball outside towards off and Dhawan pushes it back
fuller and wider, Dhawan gets room and crunches it through the covers for one
too wide outside off and shapes way even more for a wide
full and outside off, driven firmly to mid-off
full down the leg side now for another wide, Bravo struggling to get the right line
length ball outside off, Rayudu makes a bit of room and pushes it late to point
even more room and fuller, Rayudu stretches out and drives it past a diving short cover for two
angled in from length towards off stump, Rayudu defends it back without moving much
starts with a wide down the leg side
length ball outside off stump, slices it late to backward point
fuller and a bit wider, pushed with a forward lean to cover point now
slightly slower outside off, Dhawan waits for it and taps it towards cover point for one
back of length with outswing outside off, tapped to third man easily for one
134kph, room for Dhawan but it cuts after pitching and Dhawan drives but can't middle it again
123kph, he's mixing up the pace, this one's shorter outside off, Dhawan hops back to cut but can't send it beyond backward point
angled in from outside off, Rayudu stays back and defends it back
length ball towards the off stump, Rayudu defends after leaning forward
touch shorter outside off, a bit slow too and Rayudu rocks back to cut it late towards third man
he takes a step down, wants to turn the length ball to leg but gets a run on the off side after he was hit on the thigh pad after an inside edge
full on the stumps, driven down to long-on for an easy single
full and slow offcutter at 108kph on the pads, he pushes it past the bowler on the off side with a straight bat for one

I've been describing this shot all day. A little short on the off-stump channel. Dhawan camps back and steers it fine of deep third man. And ironically it's Marlon Samuels down there, who played that shot as if his life depended on it
full and a shade outside off, drives on the up through the covers
fuller and a shade outside off, gets a little nip away which makes Rayudu wary. Lets it go
shortish and it ducks back in quite sharply. Rayudu is late in getting the bat in line and the ball lobs off his thighs to the slips. Appeal, not given
flows into the fuller ball and drives it past a diving mid-off. A touch too full but not quite a half-volley. Played it on the up and went through with the stroke
pins a little width on this fuller ball and Rayudu has sliced it to the right of point. Smart shot
107 kph, change of pace lobbed in on off stump, pushed back at the bowler
too short and too wide, Rayudu sat back, waited on it and cut it well behind point. So no need to keep it down.
very little pace on this again, 110 kph offcutter on middle. Dhawan is carefully behind it
full and wide, Dhawan leans in and strokes it through the covers. Seems like that came off the bottom of the bat yet it whistled away
110kph, third slower ball of the over, good length and a shade outside off. Tapped away through point
stock ball on off stump, guided with an angled blade to point
back of a length and in the off stump channel, defended
gets forward and settles into a punch to cover
banged in short, Rayudu shuffles across on off stump, brings his front leg up off the pitch and pulls to deep square leg
115kph, nips down the track only to see a slower delivery come out, has to adjust midway through and punches through the covers

oh dear, he's rushed down the track and miscued a swipe to mid-on. He's showed some good timing till now and he seems to know it as he walks back, head thrown back, but this time he has looked to force a drill down the ground. To horrible effects
shortish and pushed across the left-hander, who is lead-footed and wafts. No edge though
offcutter on leg stump at 108 kph, Dhawan tucks it to midwicket

knocks it onto his stumps and Bravo pulls out the aeroplane! This was a good length ball in the off stump channel. Raina got forward and drives away from the body, a bit of a lazy shot that as the ball pings off the inside edge and onto his stumps. A little chest-thumping time for Bravo.
back of a length and slid down the leg side. Dhoni doesn't care about it
probes in the off stump corridor, Dhoni will not bite at the back of a length delivery
fullish on off stump, Dhoni is forward with a push to short cover. Slip also in play
banged in short again, and again he slides it down the pads. Reckon he might have planned a little too much for the left-handed Raina and is still stuck in that mode?
free-flowing drive through the covers to get him off the mark. Kochi roars (of course) A little too full from Bravo and it had too much width too
drills a fuller ball on off stump to short cover, Kieron Pollard gets his body behind it
fullish and a shade outside off, Dhawan steers it towards point
nice and tight on off stump, Dhawan is happy staying put and chopping it down to third man
gets a little lift off a short ball. It is a shade outside off and brings Dhoni up on his toes with a block. However, he was into the stroke too early and gets an inside edge towards square leg
moves around the wicket and sends a length ball down the leg side
full and on the pads again, Dhawan shuffles across and whips it away behind square leg
something seems to have bitten the West Indies bowlers. They're straying down leg every other delivery recently
139kph, full and straight, Dhoni and his wrists though make use of the angle and gets a single through midwicket
back of a good length on middle, and this one is slower too. 113 kph delivery tapped towards point
pushed through on a good length on leg stump, but it bounces. Beats Dhoni's flick
tossed up outside off, Dhoni leans in and taps it to short cover
runs down the track and turns a flighted ball off his pads to deep fine leg

that's an inside edge, it loops off his thigh and lobs so close to short leg! Credit to West Indies for that position. Pollard was taking evasive action as he saw the batsman loading up for the pull. Dives forward with his right hand when he sees the inside edge. But it falls a few inches from his fingertips
good length ball on middle, Dhawan gets in line with it off the back foot
back of a length and on the body, tucked away to square leg
switches around the wicket to the left-hander, but presents a shortish delivery outside off. Dhawan waits on the back foot and cuts it quite late. Manages to beat third man too
cramps him up with a good length ball that is angled steeply in. Dhawan was looking for a little room to slice it away again, but has to adjust his stroke
gets back and turns a shortish delivery to midwicket
a touch slower outside off, Dhawan is happy to let it go through to the keeper
whips away behind square leg, he had shuffled across on off stump to take advantage of the gap in the field inside the circle
jumps down the track and to the pitch of a loopy delivery outside off, drills it to mid-off
shimmies down the pitch again, but Benn pulls the length back. Dhoni has to settle for a defensive push into the on side
far more aggressive with his intent this time as he runs at the bowler and swings off his hips. Has a bit of a scare as he misses, but he has put his body in between the ball and the keeper
another run down the track for the mow over midwicket. That gap is left vacant to lure Dhoni in and it seems to be working. Wears another one on the pads
tossed up on middle and off, Dhoni nips down the pitch to work the ball against the turn again. Ball loops off his front pad and over silly point
pushed through quicker on off stump, Dhoni taps it to silly point. End of an excellent, and an awkward over from Benn
fuller on off stump, Dhawan pushes down the ground as his bat face closes on impact
tries to slices a short ball outside off behind point, but he had shuffled across a little too much to hamper the amount of room he could have had
a slower, good length ball on leg stump. Dhawan has tucked it to short fine leg. Not the most fluent innings from him today
leans on the front foot to a good length ball and slapped it to the sweeper on the off side
has a bit of room to work with but that wristy dab square of the wicket is not good enough to beat point
back of a length and outside off, Dhoni wafts and misses
gets down the track, and a little too close to the tossed up ball on middle. Pushes back at the bowler and Ben dives to his left rather gingerly to field it himself
backs away and the ball follows him, good turn on offer for Benn, but it was shorter in length and Dhawan is able to crunch it through the covers and they steal two
nips down the track to try and get under the ball, but isn't able to. Defence is his only option
stays back this time and blocks a good length ball on off stump
another foray down the track but his push isn't able to beat mid-on
swipes at a short ball after running down the track, manages to reach it despite it turning quite sharply and gets to his fifty. There is protection at fine leg though
good length ball on middle and off, cramping him up again. Defended
gets down the track to a good length ball that has no pace behind it. He has to wait on his stroke and then swings across the line to beat a diving midwicket. Mistimed again
fuller and outside off. It straightens too to take the outside edge of Dhoni's bat to third man
not quite short enough for the pull and Dhawan only inside edges the ball onto his pads
walks across on off stump, Sammy bowls it short and further outside it. Dhawan dabs it in front of point
fullish on off stump, Dhoni is behind it with a dead bat
oopsy, lobs up a full toss on leg stump. Dhawan, though, is happy to push it down the ground and rotate strike
stays on leg stump, rests on his back foot and slaps a quicker, shorter one though cover
flighted outside off stump, Dhawan gets forward to block
leans forward and turns a flighted ball to short midwicket
gets down the track, but Benn seems to have a sixth sense. Pulls the ball back, refuses the batsman to luxury of getting under him
so Dhawan pulls out an unorthodox solution. Even against a full toss. Scoops it over hie right shoulder as he gets down on one-knee.

middle stump is knocked back! Thats why people cry for yorkers in this format. It wasn't the perfect one though, more a fuller ball. But it was angled in at Dhoni. He had to quickly adjust from looking to flick to blocking the ball. But isn't able to, plays around it and is bowled. Sammy wheels away in celebration
what a shot! That's the best he's looked all innings. It was banged in outside off, pulled authoritatively to the midwicket boundary
short and wide outside off and Dhawan has cracked it behind point. Kochi roars in delight, but there is a sweeper in the deep
good length ball on off stump, defended off the front foot
fuller and a shade outside off, Dhawan pushes into the covers in search of a quick single. But Bravo is a little too quick
pushed through on middle and off, Dhawan gets outside off and clips it to deep fine leg

this is much slower through the air, Dhawan sees it as an opportunity to nip down the track and drill it through the covers. However, the ball stays straight and takes the outside edge past the lone slip fielder
flighted down the leg side, Dhawan sweeps but misses
good length ball on middle, tucked away towards midwicket
good length ball on middle, tucked away through midwicket
runs down the track, gets a little too close to the ball and strikes it down the ground
shuffles across and turns a good length ball to the right of short fine leg
moves across on off stump, Dhawan whips it away through square leg
full and outside off, Jaddu drives towards cover
he's pierced the gap this time. A little more width on offer this time and Jaddu leans into a drive, had to reach out quite a bit though but his timing is quite good
good length ball on middle and leg stump, tucked away into the on side
back of a good length, punched into the off side and that means drinks are back on the field and Vishal is back
halftracker on off stump, it keeps low as Dhawan goes back to pull it to deep midwicket
full on the off stump, driven down to long-on for one
almost through! Bit of flight outside off on length, Dhawan leaned forward to defend but played the wrong line and was beaten outside off

misses again and he's bowled this time! It was pretty slow through the air on length on the off stump, but Dhawan was feeling the pressure and went for the slog-sweep down on one knee, missing the ball completely which didn't turn and knocked the off stump
length ball on off stump, Bhuvi defends it back
flighted on middle and leg, pushed down to long-on for one
length ball seams in after pitching outside off, Bhuvi hops back and defends it on off
back of length this time and a touch wider, pushed towards cover
room this time outside off and it's punched to sweeper cover for one
slow and low full toss at 110kph outside off, Jadeja drives it with the angle through the covers

loud appeal for lbw as Bhuvi is struck on the back foot, the umpire says no! It was back of lenth outside off, seamed in sharply to beat the batsman by pace who stayed back and was hit near the knee roll in front of middle and leg. Bhuvi lucky to survive that one
length ball outside off, pushed to mid-off to end the over
flighted towards middle stump, Jadeja leans forward to defend and gets an edge on the leg side for one
flighted on off stump, Bhuvi defends it back
flight and turn on length on the off stump, Bhuvi defends on the leg side

he's struck again, what a match Samuels is having! He's bowling like a frontline spinner. He gave some flight outside off, Bhuvi pushed at it with an open face and the ball didn't turn, so took the outside edge to go straight into Sammy's hands at first slip
flight on offer on length but on leg stump, Mishra goes back and defends
flighted on middle and off, tucked to the leg side with the turn to get off the mark
length ball on the off stump, Mishra stays back and turns it to midwicket with the wrists
back of length and nipping it in from outside off, Mishra watches it go to the keeper
bouncer this time from outside off, Mishra ducks under it
full on off to follow the bouncer, solid defence by Mishra back to the bowler
back of length and coming in from outside off, Mishra goes on his toes to defend on the off side
makes room on the leg side, Taylor goes short and wide outside off to make it out of Mishra's reach who went for an upper cut
flighted around off stump, he leans forward and blocks
shorter outside off, Jadeja goes to the back foot and pushes it to point
flighted on length on middle and off, Jadeja blocks it back
length ball just outside off, Jadeja pushes it back towards mid-off where a misfield gives him a run
on length and outside off, pushes forward to send it to cover
he strays towards middle and leg and Mishra does well to sweep it with the turn fine down the leg side to collect four runs in the gap. Samuels won't be happy with how that over ended
full and slow delivery at 116kph outside off, Jajdeja went for a wild slog and missed
at 139kph, back of length and angling away outside off, Jadeja looks to cut but misses again, beaten by pace
bouncer to mix it up even more, Jadeja saw the short ball and pulled, but missed for the third time in a row
offcutter at 112kph around off, pushed delicately towards cover point for one
short of length with room outside off, Mishra's eyes light up, he cuts fiercely off the back foot but misses
length delivery to end the over outside off, Mishra defends it back
full and wide, a miscued drive rolls down to mid-off
on length and angling away a bit, Jadeja drives it down to long-off for one

that's like an offspinner at 108kph and the umpire's given him lbw! The slower delivery pitched well outside off and turned in sharply right towards the stumps, Mishra was bamboozled and hit on the front pad in front of off and middle. Looked out, given out. The ball even went on to hit the the base of off stump but the bails didn't budge
another offspinner, at 109kph, Mohit drove and got an inside edge past the stumps for a lucky boundary. Bravo had something to say to his CSK team-mate Mohit to make him smile
106.5 this time, well outside off on length driven to cover
full and wide outside off, he goes for a big drive but misses
slightly slow and short of length outside off, Jadeja waits for it and taps it close to himself
outside leg on length and hits the pads, leg bye for RJ after that went to point off the pad
back of length with a bit of room, Sharma sways his body out of the line and looks to cut towards point but misses
closer to off stump on similar length, he wants to punch it on the off side but misses again
makes room and slashes at this fuller delivery on off and middle, and slices it over point in the gap for four

another one falls, Mohit tries another big shot but holes out! It was full and nipping in towards off, Mohit went for a lofted drive without moving his feet and a leading edge flew high in the air and straight to third man
slower ball at 104 in the block hole outside off, tapped to point
offspinner at 99kph on middle and leg, turning away and Jadeja pushes it on the off side
short ball angled across, Jadeja pulls it towards midwicket for one
another slower one, this one goes down leg for a wide
slow and low full toss on the pads, flicked straight to square leg
fuller and outside off, Shami drives hard, is a bit late but manages a thick outside edge and that beats the third man to go for four
appeal for lbw as the offspinner turns from outside off and hits him outside leg and was going down further
falls safe! It was full outside off, Jadeja lofted it in the air with a drive and the ball fell out of mid-off's reach but he did well to keep it inside the boundary
length ball at 137kps outside off, pushed to cover where a misfield lets them complete a single easily
low full toss at 137kph around off, driven straight to cover
short ball towards the batsman, he pulls it in the air towards square leg but there's nobody there
another low full toss outside off, driven with the angle to sweeper cover
slow legcutter outside off at 106kph, Shami makes room to slam it on off but manages it to cover
back of length just outside off, Jadeja taps it softly on off for a quick one
strays down the leg side for a wide with a full delivery and Ramdin can't collect it
length ball outside off at 122kph give RJ enough time to punch it off the back foot
he wants to pull, he makes room, but he doesn't get much and slaps it to mid-on
shorter this time and angled in, Shami makes room again and misses it completely
full and angled into the pads, Shami flicks by lifting his right leg to maintain the balance and plays the flamingo shot for four
full again and this one's flicked fine off the pads to fine leg for two more
full and a bit wide, driven down a bit wide of long-off. There was a second there, probably, but Shami didn't look interested
yorker on the off stump, Shami makes room and digs it out to cover point
slower delivery down the leg side, another wide
bangs in the short ball towards leg side, Shami pulls it fine to fine leg for one
in the block hole outside off, RJ makes some room to tap it to short third man and Samuels dives to save a few runs
slower ball, Jadeja picks it and whips it for six! It came from the back of the hand, pitched outside leg and he rocked back to loft it with a pivot over the midwicket boundary for six!
on the other side this time! This one was well outside off, Jadeja waited for it cut it late between short third man and backward point to pierce the gap for four
Shami gets into the act now! Short ball to him, he opens up a bit and pulls it handsomely over the midwicket boundary for another six, the second of the innings
superb yorker, straight towards Shami's toes as he made room but well outside the leg stump
another one in the block hole, this one gets Shami's right toe as he made some room again. He looks in some pain, but is alright
clears his front leg, slaps the ball down the ground to mid-on
full and just outside off, pushed to long-off with an open face for one more
